{"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error CS0210\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"CS0210\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"CS0210\"\nms.assetid: 9f2ec1b8-6ca4-4147-b004-e3b43e7e8754\n---\n# Compiler Error CS0210\nYou must provide an initializer in a fixed or using statement declaration  \n  \n You must declare and initialize the variable in a [fixed statement](../../csharp/language-reference/keywords/fixed-statement.md). For more information, see [Unsafe Code and Pointers](../../csharp/programming-guide/unsafe-code-pointers/index.md).  \n  \n The following sample generates CS0210:  \n  \n```csharp  \n// CS0210a.cs  \n// compile with: /unsafe  \n  \nclass Point  \n{  \n   public int x, y;  \n}  \n  \npublic class MyClass  \n{  \n   unsafe public static void Main()  \n   {  \n      Point pt = new Point();  \n  \n      fixed (int i)    // CS0210  \n      {  \n      }  \n      // try the following lines instead  \n      /*  \n      fixed (int* p = &pt.x)  \n      {  \n      }  \n      fixed (int* q = &pt.y)  \n      {  \n      }  \n      */  \n   }  \n}  \n```  \n  \n The following sample also generates CS0210 because the [using statement](../../csharp/language-reference/keywords/using-statement.md) has no initializer.  \n  \n```csharp  \n// CS0210b.cs  \n  \nusing System.IO;  \nclass Test   \n{  \n   static void Main()   \n   {  \n      using (StreamWriter w) // CS0210  \n      // Try this line instead:  \n      // using (StreamWriter w = new StreamWriter(\"TestFile.txt\"))   \n      {  \n         w.WriteLine(\"Hello there\");  \n      }  \n   }  \n}  \n```\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,165],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"Compiler Error CS0210\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"CS0210\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"CS0210\"\nms.assetid: 9f2ec1b8-6ca4-4147-b004-e3b43e7e8754","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0210","nodes":[{"pos":[0,21],"content":"Compiler Error CS0210","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0210","pos":[0,21]}]}]